Class Interval

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.bioforscher.singa.core.utility.Range<java.lang.Double>
      • de.bioforscher.singa.mathematics.intervals.Interval
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Bounded<java.lang.Double>, Addable<Interval>, AdditivelyInvertible<Interval>, Invertible<Interval>, Multipliable<Interval>, Ring<Interval>, Subtractable<Interval>

    public class Interval
extends Range<java.lang.Double>
implements Ring<Interval>
    The main focus of interval in an arithmetic context is the simplest way to calculate upper and lower endpoints for the range of values of a function in one or more variables. The given lover and upper bonds are both inclusive.
